pull_request.title: Add NEON `poly_frommsg` and `poly_tomsg`
pull_request.body:
Signed-off-by: Duc Tri Nguyen <dnguye69@gmu.edu>

[//]: # (SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-4.0)
<!-- Please give a brief explanation of the purpose of this pull request. -->

Based on #47. Please review #47 first. 

There is a constant time problem with `poly_tomsg` and `poly_frommsg`. Thus, we either have to match the C implementation with the updated C code or write our own the vectorize constant time version. 

This PR implement vectorize constant time of `poly_frommsg` and `poly_tomsg`.

pull_request.title: Add CBMC as dependency to nix
pull_request.body:
Right now we are assuming that the user has installed:
 - CBMC: https://www.cprover.org/cbmc/
 - https://github.com/model-checking/cbmc-viewer
 - Litani: https://github.com/awslabs/aws-build-accumulator

This PR moves that into the nix dependencies, so the developer can just type `nix develop` to install us. 
It also allows us to make sure alle developers are running the same versions of these tools (and we can install updates when needed).
